  grammar:[
    {id:"N5L12g1",point:"〜より (comparison: A is more ~ than B)",explanation:"Noun A より Noun B + adjective = B is more [adj] than A. 電車より新幹線の方が速いです (Shinkansen is faster than train). 方が marks the winner.",examples:["東京より大阪の方が大きいです。 (Osaka is bigger than Tokyo.)","肉より魚が好きです。 (I like fish more than meat.)","バスより電車の方が便利です。 (Trains are more convenient than buses.)"],listening:"A より B = B is more than A. 方が emphasizes B.",production:"Compare 3 pairs of things using より (e.g., coffee vs tea, summer vs winter)."},
    {id:"N5L12g2",point:"〜ほど (not as ~ as) & 一番 (the most)",explanation:"A は B ほど + negative adj = A is not as [adj] as B. 一番 + adj = the most [adj]. 一番好きな (favorite).",examples:["東京は大阪ほど大きくないです。 (Tokyo is not as big as Osaka.)","一番高い山は富士山です。 (The tallest mountain is Mt. Fuji.)","一番好きな季節は秋です。 (My favorite season is autumn.)"],listening:"ほど + negative = not as ~ as. 一番 = the most.",production:"Say 3 things using ほど (not as ~ as) and 3 using 一番 (the most)."}
  ],
