  grammar:[
    {id:"N5L16g1",point:"〜たいです (want to ~)",explanation:"Verb ます stem + たいです = want to [verb]. 〜たくないです = don't want to. 行く→行きたい, 食べる→食べたい, する→したい. Only for 1st/2nd person (use たがる for 3rd).",examples:["日本へ行きたいです。 (I want to go to Japan.)","寿司を食べたいです。 (I want to eat sushi.)","まだ帰りたくないです。 (I don't want to go home yet.)"],listening:"たい = want to. Attach to verb ます stem. たくない = don't want to.",production:"Say 5 things you want to do using 〜たいです."},
    {id:"N5L16g2",point:"〜と思います (I think that ~)",explanation:"Sentence + と思います = I think that [sentence]. Used for opinions and guesses. いいと思います (I think it's good). 多分 + と思います = I think probably.",examples:["明日は晴れると思います。 (I think it'll be sunny tomorrow.)","この映画は面白いと思います。 (I think this movie is interesting.)","多分、来週は忙しいと思います。 (I think next week will probably be busy.)"],listening:"と思います = I think. Place after the opinion/guess.",production:"Give 3 opinions using 〜と思います (about weather, a movie, and your future)."}
  ],
