  grammar:[
    {id:"N5L21g1",point:"〜たら (if/when ~ happens)",explanation:"Verb た-form + ら = if/when [verb] happens. i-adj stem + かったら. na-adj + だったら. Noun + だったら. Can express one-time condition or discovery.",examples:["雨が降ったら、行きません。 (If it rains, I won't go.)","時間があったら、遊びましょう。 (If you have time, let's hang out.)","安かったら、買います。 (If it's cheap, I'll buy it.)"],listening:"たら = if/when. Attach to past form. Flexible — can be hypothetical or real.",production:"Make 5 conditional sentences using 〜たら."},
    {id:"N5L21g2",point:"〜と (when ~ happens, naturally)",explanation:"Verb dictionary form + と = when [verb] happens, [result] naturally follows. Describes habitual or natural consequences. Cannot express intention or request in the result.",examples:["春になると、花が咲きます。 (When spring comes, flowers bloom.)","このボタンを押すと、ドアが開きます。 (When you press this button, the door opens.)","夜になると、暗くなります。 (When night comes, it gets dark.)"],listening:"と = natural/habitual result. Result is inevitable. No volition in result clause.",production:"Make 3 sentences using 〜と for natural consequences."}
  ],
