  grammar:[
    {id:"N5L22g1",point:"Noun modification (verb/adjective + noun)",explanation:"In Japanese, modifiers go BEFORE the noun. Verb plain form + noun. i-adj + noun. na-adj + な + noun. Noun + の + noun. 日本語を話す人 (person who speaks Japanese). 赤い車 (red car). 親切な人 (kind person).",examples:["日本語を話す人 (a person who speaks Japanese)","昨日買った本 (the book I bought yesterday)","美味しい料理 (delicious food)"],listening:"Modifier comes before noun. Verb plain form, i-adj, na-adj + な, noun + の.",production:"Create 5 noun phrases by modifying nouns with verbs and adjectives."},
    {id:"N5L22g2",point:"〜時 (when ~ / at the time of)",explanation:"Verb plain form + 時 = when/at the time of [verb]. i-adj + 時. na-adj + な + 時. Noun + の + 時. 暇な時 (when free), 忙しい時 (when busy), 食べる時 (when eating).",examples:["暇な時に、本を読みます。 (When I'm free, I read books.)","忙しい時は、外で食べます。 (When I'm busy, I eat out.)","家に帰る時、コンビニに寄ります。 (When I go home, I stop by the convenience store.)"],listening:"時 = when. Attach to plain form. Tense in modifier reflects time relative to main clause.",production:"Make 5 sentences using 〜時 (when I'm ~, I do ~)."}
  ],
