  grammar:[
    {id:"N5L24g1",point:"N5 Grammar Review: Key Patterns",explanation:"Review of major N5 patterns: ます/です (polite), て-form (requests, joining), た (past), ない (negative), 〜たい (want), 〜と思います (think), 〜たら (conditional), 〜なければならない (must), 〜てあげる/もらう/くれる (giving/receiving), 〜たことがある (experience).",examples:["日本へ行ったことがあります。 (I have been to Japan.)","勉強しなければなりません。 (I must study.)","雨が降ったら、行きません。 (If it rains, I won't go.)"],listening:"Review all N5 patterns. Focus on te-form, conditionals, obligations, and giving/receiving.",production:"Write 10 sentences using different N5 grammar patterns you've learned."},
    {id:"N5L24g2",point:"N5 Exam Strategy",explanation:"JLPT N5 has 3 sections: 言語知識 (vocabulary+kanji+grammar), 読解 (reading), 聴解 (listening). Time management is key. Read questions first. For listening, preview options before audio starts. Eliminate wrong answers.",examples:["文字・語彙: Learn ~100 kanji, ~800 vocab.","文法: Master basic patterns (particles, verb forms, adjective conjugation).","聴解: Practice with audio daily."],listening:"N5 = 3 sections. Preview, time manage, eliminate wrong answers.",production:"Create a study plan covering vocabulary, grammar, reading, and listening for N5."}
  ],
